<TITLE> Govt to create 475 new upazila education posts </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 21 (bdnews24.com)  The government has decided to create 475 new upazila level education posts, said the prime minister's press secretary Abul Kalam Azad on Wednesday. The decision was taken at the 103rd meeting of the National Implementation Committee for Administrative Restructuring, Azad said. Decisions were taken on 10 issues in the meeting. Other decisions included: Formation a new upazila by breaking Brahmanbaria upazila. Establishment of fire brigades in six upazilasSherpur in Bogra, Srinagar in Munshiganj, Doyarampur in Natore, Chourabazar in Comilla, Harinakunda in Jheniadah and Pekua in Cox's Bazar, and fire stations in all upazilas countrywide. Creation of 113 new posts in BSTI. Establishment of police investigation centres in Bashbari of Narsingdi and Doulatkhan of Bhola. bdnews24.com/
